    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 18</em>, <em>Rise of the Runelords Player's Guide pg. 11</em>, <em>Curse of the Crimson Throne Player's Guide pg. 13</em>, <em>Pathfinder Campaign Setting pg. 209</em>, <em>Inner Sea World Guide pg. 290</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 18</em>, <em>Varisia, Birthplace of Legends pg. 14</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 12 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 6 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Martial</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Blades, Heavy; Close</p><h3>Description</h3><p>The traditional form of this tribal weapon is a short metal blade bound to the skull of a large horned lizard, but a skilled smith can craft one entirely out of metal. A traditional klar counts as a light wooden shield with armor spikes; a metal klar counts as a light steel shield with armor spikes. The klar's shield entry appears on page 12.</p>"
